.TH "hmcdrv_dev_name" 9 "hmcdrv_dev_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hmcdrv_dev_name \- provides a naming hint for a device node in /dev
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" hmcdrv_dev_name
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "umode_t *mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device for which the naming/mode hint is
.IP "mode" 12
file mode for device node created in /dev
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
See: devtmpfs.c, function \fBdevtmpfs_create_node\fP
.SH "RETURN"
recommended device file name in /dev
